        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="6">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE for all models with i6 engine</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage and/or personal injury, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        turn the engine off, set the parking brake, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Allow the engine to cool before attempting to remove the radiator or deaeration tank cap.
                        Always insulate the cap by wrapping it with a thick, heavy cloth. To prevent possible injury
                        from scalding water or steam, do not pull the pressure cap off immediately when it has been
                        loosened to the first notch. Pause momentarily to allow time for excess pressure to release
                        through the overflow tube.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain the cooling system into a suitable clean container.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Batteries expel explosive gases. Keep sparks, flames, burning cigarettes, or other ignition
                        sources away at all times. Always wear safety glasses and a face shield when working near
                        batteries to prevent personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the negative cable from the battery.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the inner fender panel on the passenger side.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the heater return hose and 45 degree fitting or shut off valve and bushing
                    reducer from the radiator.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove 3/4 inch pipe plug from the rear side of the engine front cover
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f029061">(Figure 1)</hotlnk>and install the pipe plug into the radiator port that
                    had the 45 degree fitting or shut off valve in Step 5.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">Vehicles equipped with Code 15LDP</emph>will not have a 3/4 inch pipe plug in the
                    engine front cover but will have a hose fitting. Remove the fitting and set aside for use later in
                    these instructions. Install a 3/4 inch pipe plug from the kit into the radiator port.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f029061" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g029061.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Remove Pipe Plug or Fuel Heater Hose Fitting</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">For Vehicles without Shut off Valve:</emph>
                    Install a bushing reducer and the 45 degree hose nipple that was removed from the radiator port in
                    Step 5 into the engine front cover
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f029062">(Figure 2)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f029062" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g029062.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. Install 45 Degree Fitting</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. 45 DEGREE ELBOW</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. BUSHING REDUCER</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. HOSE NIPPLE (HEATER RETURN HOSE)</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">For Vehicles with Shut Off Valve:</emph>
                    Install a bushing reducer and a 90 degree fitting into the engine front cover port then install the
                    shut off valve removed from the radiator port in Step 5
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f029063">(Figure 3)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f029063" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g029063.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3. Fittings for Heater Return Hose with Shut Off Valve</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. BUSHING REDUCER</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. 90 DEGREE ELBOW</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. SHUT OFF VALVE</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. 45 DEGREE ELBOW (HEATER RETURN HOSE)</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">For Vehicles with Fuel Heater Code 15LDP:</emph>Install a bushing reducer and pipe
                    tee into the engine front cover port. Install the pipe nipple for the fuel heater hose removed in
                    Step 6 into the top port of the tee. Install a 45 degree hose nipple into the remaining pipe tee
                    port
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f029064">(Figure 4)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f029064" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g029064.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Fittings for Heater Return and Fuel Heater Hoses</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BUSHING REDUCER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. PIPE TEE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HOSE NIPPLE (FUEL HEATER HOSE)</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. 45 DEGREE NIPPLE (HEATER RETURN HOSE)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">For Vehicles with Shut Off Valve and Fuel Heater Code 15LDP:</emph>
                Install a bushing reducer into the engine front cover port, a 90 degree elbow, and the shut off valve.
                Install a pipe tee, 45 degree elbow and hose nipple as shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f029065">Figure 5</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f029065" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g029065.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Fittings for Heater Return and Fuel Heater Hoses with Shut Off Valve</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BUSHING REDUCER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SHUT OFF VALVE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HOSE NIPPLE (FUEL HEATER HOSE)</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. 45 DEGREE ELBOW (HEATER RETURN HOSE)</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. PIPE TEE</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. 90 DEGREE ELBOW</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install insulation over the heater return hose (the hose disconnected from the radiator)
                    and route the hose down to the newly installed 45 degree hose nipple in the engine front cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the heater return hose to the 45 degree hose nipple and the fuel heater hose
                    with a spring clamp referring to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f029062">Figure 2</hotlnk>,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f029063">Figure 3</hotlnk>,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f029064">Figure 4</hotlnk>, and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f029065">Figure 5</hotlnk>
                    for the fitting set up on the vehicle being serviced.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install an extension clip to the stud on the engine front cover
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f029066">(Figure 6)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the heater return hose to the extension clip with a P-clip and nut
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f029066">(Figure 6)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f029066" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g029066.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Install P-Clip</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refill the radiator with coolant and check for leaks.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reinstall the inner fender panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Batteries expel explosive gases. Keep sparks, flames, burning cigarettes, or other ignition
                        sources away at all times. Always wear safety glasses and a face shield when working near
                        batteries to prevent personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the negative battery cable.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Run the engine up to operating temperature and check for leaks.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="8">
            <title>Service Procedure for all models with v8 engine</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage and/or personal injury park the vehicle on a flat level surface, turn
                        the engine off, set the parking brake, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Allow the engine to cool before attempting to remove the radiator or deaeration tank cap.
                        Always insulate the cap by wrapping it with a thick, heavy cloth. To prevent possible injury
                        from scalding water or steam, do not pull the pressure cap off immediately when it has been
                        loosened to the first notch. Pause momentarily to allow time for excess pressure to release
                        through the overflow tube.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain the cooling system into a suitable clean container.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Batteries expel explosive gases. Keep sparks, flames, burning cigarettes, or other ignition
                        sources away at all times. Always wear safety glasses and a face shield when working near
                        batteries to prevent personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the negative cable from the battery.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the inner fender panel on the passenger side.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect and remove the alternator.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove air cleaner housing and pipe.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove charge air cooler (CAC) hose from the CAC and the turbocharger. Cap (cover) the
                    CAC and turbocharger ports to prevent contaminants from entering.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The next Step does not require removal of the AC compressor or evacuation of the AC system.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove air conditioner (AC) compressor mounting bolts and carefully move the AC
                    compressor off the mounting bracket without causing leaks.. Secure the AC compressor with straps or
                    equivalent.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove belt tensioner and idler pulley.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove fuel line bracket
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f029067">(Figure 7)</hotlnk>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f029067" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g029067.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Remove Fuel Line Bracket</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the alternator/ AC compressor bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the pipe plug at the lower engine coolant port
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f029068">(Figure 8)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f029068" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g029068.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Remove Pipe Plug</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install 90 degree elbow fitting approximately 4 turns. This will allow wrench clearance
                    to tighten the fitting jam nut
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f029069">(Figure 9)</hotlnk>. Do not tighten the jam nut at this time.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f029069" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g029069.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Install 90 Degree Fitting (As Viewed Looking Down)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosely install the extension to the valve cover
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0290610">(Figure 10)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0290610" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g02906a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Loosely Install Extension</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new heater return pipe to the 90 degree fitting as shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0290611">Figure 11</hotlnk>. Do not tighten fitting at this time.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0290611" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g02906b.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Install Heater Return Pipe</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the P-clip around the new heater return pipe and to the extension
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0290612">(Figure 12)</hotlnk>. Tighten the nut.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0290612" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g02906c.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Install P-Clip</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the heater return hose from the radiator.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the hose fitting and bushing reducer from the radiator and replace with a 3/4
                    inch pipe plug from the kit.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Route the heater return hose down to the newly installed heater return pipe. Cut off
                    surplus hose and connect the hose to the heater return pipe with a hose clamp.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the 90 degree fitting jam nut installed in Step 13 and the compression fitting
                    installed in Step 15
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0290613">(Figure 13)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0290613" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g02906d.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Tighten Fitting</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">It is recommended that 3200 and 4200 Models with a V8 engine and heater shut off valve
                    not have the shut off valve reinstalled. If the customer demands the heater shut off valve be
                    reinstalled use the following procedure and refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0290614">Figure 14</hotlnk>:
                </para>
                <figure id="f0290614" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g02906e.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 14. Heater Shut Off Valve</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. 45 DEGREE ELBOW</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. COUPLER</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. SHUT OFF VALVE</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <seqlist>
                    <item>
                        <para>Remove the bushing from the heater shut off valve and install a coupler and two 45 degree
                            hose nipples from the kit.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Remove the splice connector in the heater supply line located on the top of the engine.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Install the shut off valve in the heater supply line.</para>
                    </item>
                </seqlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refill the radiator and check for leaks.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reinstall the air cleaner housing and pipe, alternator/ AC compressor bracket, idler and
                    belt tensioner pulleys, alternator belt and inner fender panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the negative battery cable.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Run the engine up to operating temperature and check for leaks.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
